      • runPhysicsTick

        public void runPhysicsTick()
        To put very very very very very very simply: applies a physics tick. It starts by creating a HashMap of Node and Vector2D[], where the Vector2D[] refers to the dispalcement and rotation of the Node It applies natural forces (like gravity), resolves all forces, then applies collision forces for the next tick to resolve Resolved forces are computed into displacements and rotations and added to the HashMap with their respective Node at the end, the HashMap is looped through and everything is sent to the MesageHub
